<subSubSection id="5DA66552FFCFFFC506F2FEE0FC5BFE4A" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="150336D9FFCFFFC506F2FEE0FC5BFE4A" blockId="7.[151,1436,151,429]" pageId="7" pageNumber="118">
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFCFFFC506F2FEE0FEABFE82" bold="true" box="[199,315,331,357]" pageId="7" pageNumber="118">Remarks.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="712D4B28FFCFFFC50773FEE0FD16FE82" author="Kimoto, S. &amp; Takizawa, H." box="[326,646,331,357]" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" refId="ref5709" refString="Kimoto, S. &amp; Takizawa, H. (1997) Leaf beetles (Chrysomelidae) of Taiwan. Tokai University Press, Tokyo, 581 pp." type="book" year="1997">Kimoto &amp; Takizawa (1997)</bibRefCitation>
reported that adults collected in 
<collectingRegion id="D778F83BFFCFFFC5023FFEE0FB13FE82" box="[1034,1155,331,357]" country="Taiwan" name="Kaohsiung" pageId="7" pageNumber="118">Kaohsiung</collectingRegion>
County, 
<collectingCountry id="6DAB7649FFCFFFC502C5FEE0FAD5FE82" box="[1264,1349,331,357]" name="Taiwan" pageId="7" pageNumber="118">Taiwan</collectingCountry>
, in late March laid yellowish-white eggs. To date, 
<taxonomicName id="D2BC4D5AFFCFFFC50449FEC4FCEFFE6E" authorityName=": Kimoto" authorityYear="1987" box="[636,895,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Gonioctena" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kamikawai">
<emphasis id="27C8EACBFFCFFFC50449FEC4FCEFFE6E" box="[636,895,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="118">Gonioctena kamikawai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the only known oviparous species within the nominotypical subgenus; all other species are ovoviviparous (
<bibRefCitation id="712D4B28FFCFFFC5057EFE38FC2FFE4A" author="Cho, H. - W." box="[843,959,403,429]" pageId="7" pageNumber="118" pagination="557 - 571" refId="ref5331" refString="Cho, H. - W. (2019) Redescription of mature larva and biological notes on the nominotypical subgenus Gonioctena Chevrolat (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae: Chrysomelinae) from South Korea. Zootaxa, 4544 (4), 557 - 571. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4544.4.6" type="journal article" year="2019">Cho 2019</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
